status_message:
We want your photos! Memorial Day is a day for remembering the men and women who died while serving in the United States Armed Forces (unlike Veterans Day which honors all who served, living and dead).

This year, MSN News will mark Memorial Day with photos of those who died in service to their country. If you would like to share a photo of a loved one who died in the military, please send it (digital copy only) to us via a message here on Facebook.

We will use as many as we can in a slideshow on MSN News. The slideshow, and/or individual photos, also will be posted on Facebook, Tumblr and Twitter.

Please include as much of the following information as possible for the person in the photo: name, year of birth, year of death, branch of service, dates of service, cause of death and your relationship to the person.

Also, when submitting images to MSN News, include your name. Please note: By submitting photos and art to MSN News, you are giving us the right to use those images on MSN News properties including MSN News' Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and MSNNews.com.

Thank you! We look forward to seeing your photos.
link_name: Timeline Photos
